<!-- Definitions and Interpretation section = contract legend. Nothing that is undefined should be capitalised unless it is a proper noun-->
<a_left_sidehead>Definitions &amp; Interpretation</a_left_sidehead>
<para_1>In this Contract, unless the subject or context otherwise requires:-</para_1>
    <definition>Applicable Law	means any applicable statute, statutory instrument, by-law, order, regulatory requirement, directive, regulation, or law (including common or civil law, judgment, demand, order or decision of a court or competent tribunal);</definition>
    <definition>Business	means any of the proprietary business, undertakings, services, assets, and activities which the Company may now or hereafter engage in, including those relating to and/or arising from <?= data.company.business_activity ?> and all (actual or demonstrably anticipated) research and development relating thereto;</definition>
    <definition>Company	includes any of its affiliates, subsidiaries, successors, and assigns;</definition>
    <definition>Company Account	means the Company's corporate bank account or bitcoin account, as may be indicated by the Company from time to time as its bank account under this Contract;</definition>
    <definition>Contractor Account	means the Contractor's bank and/or Bitcoin account specified by Contractor for her receipt of Fees under this Contract;</definition>
    <definition>Competitor	means any third party engaged in and/or carrying on business activities which are similar to and/or competitive with the Business;</definition>
    <definition>Confidential Information	means all Information, which is confidential to the Company, is treated as confidential by the Company, or which a reasonably prudent person under the circumstances should expect to be treated as confidential, as well as all (i) non-public and/or proprietary Information relating to all or any part of the Business or the Company, including the organisation, operations, dealings, property, assets, technology, activities, services, personnel, know-how, trade secrets, past or present customers or users, financial affairs, management, administration, technical information, Rights, or other proprietary business designations used or owned by the Company; and (ii) any output, analyses, compilations, studies, documents, or materials that contain or otherwise reflect Information described under (i) of this definition;</definition>
    <definition>Effective Date	means the earlier of (i) the date on which all Parties have executed this Contract, and (ii) <?= data.alternative_effective_date?>;</definition>
    <definition>Engagement Term	means the term of <?= data.engagement_term?> commencing on the Effective Date - where applicable, shall include such term as extended in accordance with Clause <xref to="Extension"/> below - and terminating upon the expiration of such term as applicable, in each case, unless otherwise earlier terminated under this Contract;</definition>
    <definition>Fees	means the fees payable by Company to Contractor as set out under Clause <xref to="Fees"/>, for the Contractor's provision and/or performance of the Services;</definition>
    <definition>GitHub	means the Company's GitHub repository at <u><?=data.company.github_url?></u> and such other (i) Github repositories, (ii) derivative repositories, and/or (iii) associated repositories which the Company uses or directs Contractor to;</definition>
    <definition>Information	means information and data (whether recorded or not, and if recorded, in whatever form on whatever media);</definition>
    <definition>Rights	means (i) trade marks, service marks, registered designs, trade and business names (including domain names and email address names), unregistered trade marks and service marks, copyrights, database rights, know-how, rights in designs, and patents; (ii) applications of and for any of each of the rights described under (i) in whatever form on whatever media (including computer output, computer program, web application and web service); (iii) rights under licenses, consents, orders, statutes, or otherwise in relation to a right described under (i) and (ii) of this definition; and (iv) rights of the same or similar effect or nature as, or to those rights described in this definition;</definition>
    <definition>Services	means the services which Contractor provides to and/or performs for the Company during the Engagement Term as set out under Clause <xref to="Services"/>;</definition>
    <definition>Slack	means the Company's <span_smallcaps>slack</span_smallcaps> application at http://legalese.slack.com; and </definition>
    <definition>Work	means all Rights, notes, memoranda, records, correspondence, inventions, discoveries, designs, processes, formulæ, innovations, developments, improvements, copyright works (including without limitation, files, computer software, computer programs, articles, reports, drawings, technical drawings, blueprints, advertisements, sales materials, plans, and logos), and the like of whatsoever nature - in each case, including all copies thereof - made, compiled, acquired, discovered, conceived, developed, reduced to practice, and/or expressed in tangible form by the Contractor (whether solely or jointly with other persons, and whether directly or indirectly) during the Engagement Term, (i) arising out of, relating to, or in pursuance of this Contract, or (ii) relating to the Business, finances, or affairs of the Company, or any member of the Company, or (iii) which constitutes works for hire based (whether directly or indirectly) on any item of Confidential Information (whether or not patentable, registrable, and/ or copyrightable), and in each case, shall also include any applications for and/or of any of those rights that is assigned or that may be assigned to the Company under this Contract or otherwise.</definition>

