<a_left_sidehead>Interpretation</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para>Unless the context otherwise requires or is expressly stated by Company to Contractor as being to the contrary, in this Contract:-</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>words importing the singular include the plural and vice versa;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>words importing a gender include every gender;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>references to persons include bodies corporate or unincorporated, any state or any agency thereof, and any other entity, and vice versa;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>headings, marginal sidenotes, and graphic art are for ease of reference only and have no legal effect;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>references to Clauses are to clauses of this Contract, and references to this Contract include any schedules, amendments, and supplementals thereto;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>references to Company shall include its successors and permitted assigns;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>the words and phrases "other", "including" and "in particular" do not limit the generality of any preceding words, and the words which follow them will not be construed as being limited in scope to the same class as the preceding words where a wider construction is possible;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>references to a time of day are to Singapore time, and '<b>$</b>' or '<b>dollars</b>' denotes Singapore dollars; and</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>references to a statutory provision include such provision and any regulations made in pursuance thereof, from time to time modified and/or re-enacted, whether before or after the Effective Date so far as such modification or re-enactment applies or is capable of applying to and/or in connection with this Contract.</numbered_3_para>

<!--Consideration tells you what is being exchanged between the parties-->
<a_left_sidehead>Consideration &amp; payment terms</a_left_sidehead>
<numbered_2_para xname="Fees"><b>Consideration</b></numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_3_para>During the Engagement Term, in consideration of the fees at a <b>monthly</b> rate of <b><?= data.monthly_fees ?></b> ("<b>Fees</b>") to be paid by the Company to Contractor, Contractor agrees to provide to and/or perform for the Company, the Services - as an independent contractor - in accordance with this Contract.</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Fees paid by Company to Contractor shall constitute the full and only payment Contractor is entitled to in respect of the Services.</numbered_3_para>

<numbered_2_para><b>Timing of payment</b></numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_3_para>During the Engagement Term, Fees shall be paid by Company to Contractor by the last day of each month, provided that where applicable, Fees shall be pro-rated for any partial month resulting from the termination of this Contract prior to its expiration or otherwise.</numbered_3_para>

<numbered_2_para><b>Method of payment</b></numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Company's payment of Fees to Contractor shall be either via:</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_4_para>a transfer from Company's Account to Contractor's Account, and in respect of Bitcoin payments, the amount of Bitcoin shall be calculated by Company based on the prevailing BTC/SGD rate, as quoted at https://www.google.com/finance?q=btcsgd at any time on either the day of or the day before before the transfer; or</numbered_4_para>
    <numbered_4_para>such other means as Parties may agree in writing between them.</numbered_4_para>
<a_left_sidehead>Term</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para xname="Engagement Term"> <b>Initial Term</b></numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>This Contract shall become effective upon the Effective Date and determine <?= data.engagement_term ?> therefrom, unless earlier terminated under this Contract or otherwise.</numbered_3_para>

<numbered_2_para xname="Extension"><b>Extension</b></numbered_2_para>
<!-- Made it such that the extension term will be the length of the original term-->
  <numbered_3_para>This Contract may be extended on identical terms for a maximum of <?= data.engagement_term ?> upon written agreement between Contractor and two (2) directors of the Company. In such event, the initial Engagement Term shall be extended accordingly.</numbered_3_para>

<!--A little longwinded, I know. But these are the kinda things that we can set out from the outset based on what we know courts / regulators interpret as distinguishing factors between contractors and employees. Of course when push comes to shove, what actually happens between the parties and how they actually conduct the relationship has more bearing-->
<a_left_sidehead>Relationship between the Parties</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para>The Parties hereby accept to the fullest extent permissible under Applicable Law, that under this Contract:-</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>Contractor shall provide Services to and/or perform the Services for the Company on her own account as a self-employed independent contractor and nothing in this Contract shall be construed as (i) creating a joint venture, partnership, franchise relationship, employer/employee relationship, or such other similar relationship between the Parties, or (ii) authorising either Party to act as the agent of the other;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>save where Company at its absolute discretion agrees to provide otherwise on an <i>ad-hoc</i> and one-time basis, Contractor shall independently acquire and control, at her own expense, the tools, equipment, software, means, supplies, details, manner, methods, working place, and such other factors of production (including any means required to support such factors of production) as she may require to provide and/or perform the Services and fulfill her obligations under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>Contractor has the right to perform and/or provide the Services and fulfill her obligations under this Contract from any place and at such times as the Contractor shall determine at her own discretion;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>Contractor shall bear all taxes on her earnings as required by Applicable Law, and shall be solely and fully responsible for the calculation and prompt payment of any applicable taxes to the home and host tax authorities as determined by her local taxation legislation, and the Company bears no tax liabilities for Contractor nor shall Company pay any taxes (including any withholding taxes) for Contractor; and</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>Contractor has no entitlements to any overtime pay, vacation pay, sick leave, retirement benefits, social security, employee compensation, health or disability benefits, unemployment insurance benefits, or employee benefits of any kind.</numbered_3_para>

<a_left_sidehead xname="Services">Services</a_left_sidehead>
<!--TODO: at some point we should automate these into the form so that they can be easily replaced for different roles. The input should bear in mind the context in which the services will be described-->
<numbered_2_para>During the Engagement Term, Contractor shall on a full-time non-exclusive basis, specifically in the role of <b><?= data.role ?></b> for the purposes of the Business and/or <?= data.purpose ?>, devote her time, energy, abilities and resources as may be necessary, expedient, and efficient, to resolve the issues and/or milestones set out at GitHub and such other means and systems suggested by the Company for requirements management, issue tracking, document management, source control, and other support or development functions, and in each case within any timeframes specified therein. Company may from time to time, suggest priorities for such issues and/or milestones via Slack, GitHub, or emails. ("<b>Services</b>").</numbered_2_para>

<a_left_sidehead>Representations</a_left_sidehead>

<!--Factual representations from the Company-->
<numbered_2_para>Company hereby represents that:-</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_3_para>it has the power and capacity to enter into this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>it will make timely payment of the Fees when such Fees as applicable are due;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>it shall use reasonable endeavours to notify Contractor of any changes to its procedures affecting Contractor's obligations under this Contract; </numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>in view of Company possessing critical knowledge of the operations and the Business, it shall respond and cooperate with Contractor in making such knowledge available to Contractor in a timely fashion to facilitate Contractor's provision and/or performance of the Services under this Contract; and </numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>during the Engagement Term, it shall provide such other assistance to the Contractor as the Company (at its sole and absolute discretion) may deem reasonable and/or appropriate.</numbered_3_para>

<!--from the Contractor now-->
<numbered_2_para>Contractor hereby represents that:-</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she has the power, capacity, competence, ability, and experience to enter into this Contract, provide and/or perform the Services and fulfill her obligations under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>her performance and/or provisions of the Services and fulfillment of her obligations under this Contract does not and will not breach any other agreement to which she is a party;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she has not entered and will not during the Engagement Term enter into any oral or written agreement in conflict with any provisions under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she will in her provision and/or performance of the Services, including any undertakings, commencement, or progress made thereto, promptly communicate the same to the Company (at least within 2 days of occurrence) to the Company via Slack, GitHub, and/or such other means of communication that Company uses for similar purposes;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>save where communicated to Contractor via the Company's director(s) on behalf of the Company, she acknowledges and accepts that all other communications (including instructions, direction, suggestions, promises, assurances, confirmations) in respect of this Contract or outside the scope of Services, shall be invalid and unenforceable against the Company;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>the Services will be provided and/or performed in accordance with and will not violate any Applicable Law (and where applicable, she has obtained all permits and/or permissions and done all such acts as may be required to comply with such Applicable Law) or any of the Company's policies and directives as may be communicated via (or set out by the Company in) Github, Slack, or Company's shared Google Drive;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>the Company shall not be required or expected to supervise (but may at its own discretion mentor or guide) the Contractor in her performance of the Services and/or her obligations under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>the Company shall not be required to hire or pay any assistants or additional persons to help Contractor perform the Services and her obligations under this Contract; and</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she will seek timely review and comments on her deliverables, performance and/or provision of the Services, and her fulfillment of obligations under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she will notify Company immediately of any change in her representations under this Contract or change in her abilities to fulfill any of her obligations under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she will promptly communicate to Company any gaps in her knowledge of the operations, the Business, or knowledge required for her provision and/or performance of the Services or fulfillment of her obligations under this Contract, and thereafter, use her best efforts to actively address and resolve such gaps;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she will write, create, and update any documentation (whether or not such documentation was created by her) in respect of her provision and/or performance of the Services, so as to enable other independent contractors, employees of the Company, or community members of the Company to, as the case may be, take over, collaborate with Contractor, and/or work on improving or adapting the subject matter of such Services; </numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she will actively work with and communicate with Company's personnel (including its employees, directors, contractors, external vendors, service provider, etc.), in particular, where there is an overlap or interaction in the scope or services rendered; and </numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>she is responsible for and will accordingly, pay for all ordinary, extraordinary, or necessary expenses (whether for herself or otherwise) arising out of or relating to this Contract, her provision and/or performance of the Services, and/or her obligations under this Contract.</numbered_3_para>

<!-- Clarification about ownership of work done during the Engagement Term -->
<a_left_sidehead>Ownership of Work</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para>Contractor acknowledges and accepts that, to the fullest extent permissible under Applicable Law - and save where otherwise agreed to in writing by the Company - during the Engagement Term and after, Work, including any and all materials prepared by Contractor under this Contract shall be considered proprietary to the Company.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para xname="Take Action">Where any Work or Rights are not deemed proprietary to the Company under Applicable Law, Contractor hereby assigns to the Company all of its Right, title, interest in and to Work (and any other Rights relating thereto). Contractor shall also without compensation and forthwith upon demand, whether during the Engagement Term or otherwise, execute and deliver to the Company any applications, specifications, oaths, assignments, recordations, or any instruments of transfer, and take such action as may be requested by Company, to secure and ensure protection of such of Company's rights and interest and to effect the transfer of such Rights, title, and/or interests to the Company.</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>Actions under Clause <xref to= "Take Action" /> include the signing of documents and giving of testimony required in the course of the Company applying for or maintaining any Rights, or in the course of any litigation or other legal proceeding related to Work (and any Rights relating thereto) anywhere in the world.</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>Contractor's obligation to execute or cause to be executed any such instrument, papers or take any action described under this Clause <xref to= "Take Action" /> shall continue after the termination of this Contract until the expiration of the last of such Rights in any country in the world.</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para xname="license">If, under Applicable Law, Contractor is unable to assign all or any part of such Rights to the Company, or if approval of such assignment is required from a government authority and such approval is not granted, Contractor hereby licenses to the Company such Rights as cannot be assigned, so that the Company shall have the complete right to use and right to exploit the applicable Work (and any Rights relating thereto), and any modified or derivative works thereof. Unless otherwise agreed between the Parties in writing, the license described under this Clause <xref to="license" /> shall be perpetual, free of charge, sub-licensable, irrevocable, exclusive (excluding both the Contractor and all third parties), worldwide, and transferable.</numbered_3_para>
<!--I am sceptical if the clause below is enforceable in Singapore. It is effectively executing a POA (which by default has to executed as a deed), but this is also a long-distance, remote contract for a fully online, remote-first company that expressly specifies software applications/online platforms as the default mode of communication-->
  <numbered_2_para>Contractor hereby irrevocably designates and appoints the Company (including its duly authorized officers and agents, as may be relevant or required) as her agent and attorney in fact, but only to the extent where the Company is unable - because of the Contractor's mental or physical incapacity or unavailability or for any other reason - to secure the Contractor's signature to apply for or to pursue any rights or interest protecting application covering the Rights or Works under this Contract, to act for and on her behalf and stead to execute and file any such applications, and to do all other lawfully permitted acts to further the application for, prosecution, issuance, maintenance or transfer of such rights or interest with the same legal force and effect as if personally executed by the Contractor.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Contractor further agrees not to exercise any rights or interests in Rights and/or Works that under Applicable Law cannot be assigned or licensed to the Company pursuant to the foregoing, including but not limited to right to claim authorship and the right not to suffer false attribution of authorship, except with the prior written consent of the Company.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>At any time (whether during the Engagement Term or after), where Contractor intends to integrate and/or incorporate any of her proprietary rights and/or previous work in furtherance of her provision and/or performance of the Services and fulfillment her obligations under this Contract, such intention shall be communicated in writing to the Company prior to any such intended integration and/or incorporation. Where Company, at its sole and absolute discretion consents to such integration and/or incorporation, Contractor hereby grants Company an exclusive, worldwide, royalty-free, perpetual, irrevocable license to use, distribute, modify, publish, sub-license, and/or otherwise exploit such integration and/or incorporation in connection with the Business of the Company.</numbered_2_para>

<a_left_sidehead>Conflicts of Interest</a_left_sidehead>
<numbered_2_para>Contractor acknowledges that as an independent contractor, she is free to engage in other activities, including any activities in the role of <?= data.role ?> for any other persons during the Engagement Term  that, so long as:-</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor is able to continue and fulfill her obligations as set out under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor's participation in or pursuance of such other activity, does not conflict or is not otherwise incompatible with Contractor's obligations or her performance and/or provision of Services under this Contract; and</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor has notified the Company of her participation in and/or pursuance of such activities.</numbered_3_para>

<a_left_sidehead>Dealing with Confidential Information and Work</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para>The Company does not give any warranty or representation to Contractor as to the accuracy or completeness of Confidential Information, and Company shall not be liable for any damages, claims, or losses resulting from the use of Confidential Information.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Contractor hereby undertakes that during the Engagement Term and after, she shall protect Work and Confidential Information using at least the same standard of care she applies to her own proprietary and/or confidential Information (but no less than reasonable care), and to the extent not prohibited by Applicable Law, ensure that Confidential Information and Work which she accesses, create, amends, or otherwise deals with, is stored, handled, and maintained in such a way as to prevent unauthorised access or disclosure.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Save where expressly permitted under this Contract or required for Contractor's provision and/or performance of the Services or her fulfillment of her obligations under this Contract, Contractor shall not copy, reproduce, adapt, modify, translate, manufacture, market, publish, distribute, sell, license (or sublicense), transfer, rent, lease, transmit, broadcast, display, use, or otherwise exploit (i) any Work or Confidential Information; or (ii) disclose any or Work or Confidential Information to any person.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Nothing in this Contract, whether by implication or otherwise, and whether directly or indirectly, shall or be construed as granting to or conferring upon Contractor any Rights (whether to Work, Confidential Information, or otherwise).</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Contractor hereby acknowledges and accepts that Work and Confidential Information, and all Rights therein, are and shall remain the sole and exclusive property of the Company.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>Save where expressly permitted under this Contract or otherwise agreed to by the Company in writing, Contractor hereby undertakes to:-</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>hold in strictest confidence the Confidential Information;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>take all steps (including any steps that Company may direct or suggest) to prevent any unauthorised reproduction, duplication, or copying of Confidential Information and Work by any person;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>take all steps (including any steps that Company may direct or suggest) to ensure that documents and/or items of work-in-progress that embody Work or Confidential Information are kept and maintained securely (including, using disk encryption and two-factor authentication protection whenever such options are available);</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>not create derivative works from, provide access electronically to, or enter into computer memory beyond the Company's control, Work or Confidential Information (including any portion or copy thereof) in any form; and </numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>not apply for, or apply to register, any Rights in or related to Confidential Information or Work, in Singapore or any other country or region.</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_2_para>For the avoidance of doubt, Confidential Information shall not include any information or data which:-</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>at the date of its disclosure can be proved by documentary evidence to be Information which is publicly available or which subsequently becomes publicly available other than by consequence of Contractor's breach of this Contract or breach of any confidentiality obligations by a third party; or</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>at the date of its disclosure can be proved by documentary evidence to be already rightfully available and/or in the possession of Contractor prior to Contractor's receipt of the same from Company, and that the same had not been acquired (whether directly or indirectly) from the Company or any person known to Contractor as being under an obligation of confidence; or</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>is compelled to be disclosed by Applicable Law of a competent jurisdiction to which Contractor is subject, or by a court of competent jurisdiction, regulator, or any competent supervisory or regulatory body to which Contractor may be subject, provide that where Contractor is so compelled, she shall prior to making any disclosure and save where prohibited under Applicable Law, promptly inform Company and take Company's instructions as to the form, nature, content, and extent of any proposed disclosure; or</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>is developed by Contractor independently without the use and/or reference to Confidential Information.</numbered_3_para>

<a_left_sidehead>Termination of Contract</a_left_sidehead>

<b_left_sidehead_nonum>Termination without cause</b_left_sidehead_nonum>
  <numbered_2_para>The Company shall be entitled to terminate this Contract upon the issuance of not less than <b>14 days' prior written notice</b> to Contractor at any time.</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_2_para>The Contractor shall be entitled to terminate this Contract by giving the Company no less than <b>1 months' prior written notice</b>.</numbered_2_para>

<b_left_sidehead_nonum>Termination by summary notice</b_left_sidehead_nonum>
<numbered_2_para>The Company shall be entitled (but not obliged) at any time to terminate the Contract with immediate effect by summary notice where Company reasonably determines that:-</numbered_2_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor has committed a serious or material breach of or failure in her obligations under this Contract; or</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor has repeatedly breached her obligations under this Contract, and where such breach is capable of being remedied, despite Company's notice to Contractor to remedy such breach, Contractor has failed to promptly remedy such breach to Company's sole and absolute satisfaction; or</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor commits an act or engages in conduct which brings or would bring herself or the Company into disrepute or such act or conduct materially conflicts with Company's established policies, code of conduct, and ethos; or</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor commits or engages in any act of misconduct, dishonesty, fraud, misrepresentation, breach of confidentiality obligations under this Contract, or violates any laws and/or regulations in any jurisdiction; or</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor is convicted of any criminal offence, other than an offence which in the absolute opinion of the Company does not adversely affect Contractor's position as an independent contractor, her performance and/or provision of the Services, or her fulfillment of her obligations under this Contract; or</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor in the absolute opinion of the Company becomes of unsound mind and/or incapacitated to provide and/or perform the Services and/or fulfill its obligations under this Contract; or</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>Contractor makes or has a bankruptcy application or petition served on her or makes any arrangement or composition with her creditors generally; or</numbered_3_para>
  <numbered_3_para>it becomes illegal for the Company to engage Contractor as an independent contractor whether under this Contract or otherwise.</numbered_3_para>

<numbered_2_para>The termination of this Contract howsoever arising shall not affect such of the terms hereof as are expressed to operate or have effect after the Engagement Term, and shall be strictly without prejudice to any right of action or remedy which the Company may have.</numbered_2_para>

<a_left_sidehead>Effects of Termination or Determination</a_left_sidehead>
  <numbered_2_para>Upon determination and/or termination of this Contract for whatever reason, Contractor shall:-</numbered_2_para>
    <numbered_3_para>immediately relinquish all access and/or rights given to her specifically for her provision and/or performance of the Services or fulfillment of her obligations under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>not at any time thereafter, represent herself (whether actively or by omission, directly or indirectly) as being in any way connected or affiliated to the Company or engaged in any Business or affairs of the Company as under this Contract;</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>where Company requires, promptly return to the Company all forms of Confidential Information and Work, including any and all copies and extracts thereof, and delete any such items in the Contractor's personal possession and prohibit the Contractor's subsequent personal access; and</numbered_3_para>
    <numbered_3_para>where Company requires, not make or retain any copies or extracts of any Confidential Information or Work, and agree to provide written confirmation and supporting evidence to the Company of such undertaking.</numbered_3_para>

